WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.080
And I was wondering, what advice do you have for those organizations that are really just

00:00:04.080 --> 00:00:07.240
starting to explore, implement People Analytics?

00:00:07.240 --> 00:00:14.840
I think if you're just starting a team, developing good relationships with your other leaders

00:00:14.840 --> 00:00:20.440
in HR to find out what are their big concerns, what are their pain points where we could

00:00:20.440 --> 00:00:24.600
apply analytics to help solve problems would be a big part of that, and that will help

00:00:24.600 --> 00:00:28.360
you decide what direction you want to take in building your team if you're just getting

00:00:28.360 --> 00:00:30.580
started.

00:00:30.580 --> 00:00:35.759
And from there, if you can find the HR leaders, if they are in touch with the business units,

00:00:35.759 --> 00:00:39.599
they can also tell you what are the pain points of the different business units.

00:00:39.599 --> 00:00:45.880
And from there, you can decide how large a team you need or what do you need people that

00:00:45.880 --> 00:00:50.759
specialize in different areas and having a good relationship with each of those different

00:00:50.759 --> 00:00:51.480
business units.

